Reset PC in Safe File Mode (Keep My Files)
🔌 1. Insert bootable USB
Plug your USB into the PC
Turn ON / Restart
⌨️ 2. Open Boot Menu

Press repeatedly:

F12 / ESC / F9 / DEL (depends on laptop)

Select your USB drive

🪟 3. Windows Setup screen
Choose language → Click Next
🛠️ 4. Click Repair
Click “Repair your computer” (bottom-left)
🔄 5. Go to Reset
Click Troubleshoot
Click Reset this PC
🟢 6. Choose “Keep my files”

👉 This is what you want

✔ Keeps:

Documents
Pictures
Desktop files

❌ Removes:

Installed apps/software
Old password
⚙️ 7. Choose reinstall type
Select Local reinstall (recommended)
▶️ 8. Start process
Click Reset
PC will restart automatically

⏳ Wait 20–60 minutes

🎉 9. After reset
No old password anymore
Your personal files are still there
You can create a new password
